JOHANNESBURG - The Black Lawyers Association (BLA) on Tuesday condemned politicians who have accused the judiciary of overreach. This comes after a court judgment set aside the appointment of NPA boss Shaun Abrahams last week. ANC Women’s League President Bathabile Dlamini at the weekend accused the judiciary of trying to control government. WATCH: Justice factor : Justice Malala is in conversation with ANC secretary-general Gwede Mantashe Part 3 of 3 The association says the claims are unwarranted and should be challenged. eNCA specialist reporter Karyn Maughan says Dlamini's statements are problematic.
